      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the almond cream",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} until pale. Beat in the {{free-range-eggs}} (for the filling) and {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{ground-almonds}} and {{plain-flour}}. Add the {{dark-rum}} if using. Refrigerate for 20 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cut the pastry discs",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Unroll the first sheet of {{puff-pastry}} and cut a 24 cm disc using a plate as a guide. Place on a lined baking tray. Cut a 26 cm disc from the second sheet.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and hide the fève",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mound the cold almond cream in the centre of the base disc, leaving a 4 cm border. Push a small oven-safe ceramic charm or a dried broad bean into the filling, not near the centre, where it might be cut by a knife. Brush the border with the beaten {{free-range-eggs}} (for egg wash). Lay the larger disc over the top and press the edges together firmly. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Score, glaze, and bake, 28 to 32 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Brush the top of the galette with egg wash. Using the tip of a very sharp knife, score curved arcs from the centre outward, 8 arcs, curving in the same direction, cutting only 2 to 3 mm deep. Do not cut through. Bake for 28 to 32 minutes until deep golden and puffed. Serve warm with a paper crown.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
